Structured Data against each job so google can identify your jobs. It also does the indexing of the jobs on google, which means you can index your job URL on google when you publish/update and remove a job.</p>\n<p>For the functioning of Google Job Search, please fill the following details in the Location Details meta box on the job detail page:</p>\n<ul class=\"d-ul list2\">\n<li>Street Address</li>\n<li>Address Region(State/Province)</li>\n<li>Postal Address</li>\n<li>Country</li>\n<li>Currency</li>\n<li>Salary</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also provide Company information in meta fields which are located below the job description.</p>\n<p>For Google Indexing, please first read the <a href=\"https://market.presstigers.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Job-Search-and-Indexing-API-Add-on-Usage-Guideline.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">installation guide</a> and then add the JSON file code under Job Board&gt; Settings&gt; Google Indexing API tab.</p>\n<div style=\"background: #e8eaf6; padding: 10px;\">\n<p><b><span style=\"color: #ff0000; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Important: </span></b>Google does not guarantee that your structured data will show up in search results, even if your page is marked up correctly according to the <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://search.google.com/test/rich-results\">Rich Results Test</a>. Please go through Google\'s <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/advanced/structured-data/sd-policies\">general structured data guidelines</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Note: <em>This add-on needs a 20MB upload limit. If you are facing a maximum execution timeout error then please increase \"max_execution_time\" in your server configuration(php.ini).</em></strong></p>\n\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:132:\"<p>This add-on is responsible to integrate the Google Structured Data against each job and perform the google indexing of jobs.</p>\n\";s:15:\"reviews_allowed\";b:1;s:14:\"average_rating\";s:4:\"0.00\";s:12:\"rating_count\";i:0;s:11:\